	"name": "Searing Fire",
	"type": "feature",
	"img": "icons/magic/fire/explosion-embers-evade-silhouette.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>At 3rd level, your fire burns the flesh of your enemies relentlessly. Whenever you deal fire damage to a creature, you can make it burn. The creature takes 1d6 fire damage at the start of their turn for one minute or until they or another creature uses an action to stop the fire. The damage increases to 2d6 at 6th level. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per short rest.</p>",
